Node.Notes: Uncertain what mahalath leannoth means. Often assumed to be the tune. Perhaps a psalm related to self-abasement over illness.

Uncertain if all references refer to the same Heman: 1k5:11 mentioned with Ethan the Ezrahite (ps89:1) as one of the famous wise men of Solomon’s reign; the king’s seer in 1c25:5 and mentioned along with Ethan in 1c15:17, 19 as among the Korahite Levitical singers. Also a singer in 1c6:18–23 [6:33–38] and ancestry traced back to Korah.
The reference to Heman here and Ethan (ps89:1) as Ezrahites are mysteries as no direct connection between the Ezrahites and the Korahites is known elsewhere.

Syntax uncertain. Tree assumes "By day I cry out, in the night [I cry out] before you." Possibly "in the night [I am] before you." Many disregard syntax and translate sense "day and night I cry out before you."
Uncertain. Could mean strength or help (with ancient versions).
Uncertain. Tree assumes juxtaposition of 3 related places. Alternatively, each could be in apposition to the previous place name in succession.
